    <ul>
      <li><p>Convenience  the form to make the change is always visible (Collaborators)</p></li>
      <li><p>Disclosed  the form to make changes is hidden until requested (SSH keys)</p></li>
      <li><p>Complex  changes are made within a modal (2FA, Credit cards)</p></li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="u-margin-Txl u-padding-Tl">Convenience</h3>
    <p>Convenient, always visible forms should be used when the input form is very simple (one or two elements) and where it does not distract from the content of the view.</p>

    <div class="purple-box u-margin-Tl">
      <img class="img-responsive" src="/images/collaborators-1.png"/>
    </div>
    <h4>The form to add a new collaborator is always visible</h4>

    <h3 class="u-margin-Txl u-padding-Tl">Disclosed</h3>
    <p>Disclosed forms should house more complex inputs (such as multiple text inputs, text areas, radio buttons etc) or can be used where adding data is an uncommon/infrequent function of the view.</p>

    <div class="purple-box u-margin-Tl">
      <img class="img-responsive" src="/images/ssh-add.gif"/>
    </div>
    <h4>The form to add an SSH key is hidden until the user discloses it</h4>

    <h3 class="u-margin-Txl u-padding-Tl">Complex</h3>
    <p>Complex forms may span multiple pages (wizards) or may contain other content that merits an entirely focused view. These may be shown on a new page or within a modal.</p>

    <div class="bg-modal purple-box u-margin-Tl u-text-center u-padding-Al">
      <img class="u-margin-Vl" src="/images/creditcard.png" style="max-width: 626px; width: 100%;"/>
    </div>

    <h3 class="u-margin-Txl u-padding-Tl">Inline editing</h3>
    <p>For single inputs (like name, email address in our profile), the input can be put in an editable state just by clicking on it.</p>

    <div class="purple-box u-margin-Tl u-text-center u-padding-Am">
      <img src="/images/profile-edit.gif" style="max-width: 530px; width: 100%;"/>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

